<DIV1 TYPE="song">
<HEAD>SONG</HEAD>
<BYLINE>Set by Mr. <HI>John Eccles,</HI> and Song by Mrs. <HI>Hodg&s;on.</HI></BYLINE>
<LG N="1">
<HEAD>I.</HEAD>
<L>_LOVE's but the Frailty of the Mind,</L>
<L>When 'tis not with Ambition join'd;</L>
<L>A &s;ickly Flame, which if not fed expires;</L>
<L>And feeding, wa&s;les in Self-con&s;uming Fires.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="2">
<PB N="34" REF="41">
<HEAD>II.</HEAD>
<L>'Tis not to wound a wanton Boy</L>
<L>Or am'rous Touth, that gives the Joy;</L>
<L>But 'tis the Glory to have pierc'd a Swain,</L>
<L>For whom inferior Beauties &s;igh'd in vain.</L>
