</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Wit.</SPEAKER>
<P>Not po&s;itively mu&s;t&mdash;But it may&mdash;It may.</P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Pet.</SPEAKER>
<P>Yes, it po&s;itively mu&s;t, upon Proof po&s;$ive.</P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Wit.</SPEAKER>
<P>Ay, upon Proof po&s;itive it mu&s;t; but upon Proof pre|&s;umptive
